0037#STR0037#ALL#From Cost Center?
0038#STR0038#ALL#Cost center code. The field 
0039#STR0039#ALL#can be left empty to consider 
0040#STR0040#ALL#codes since the first one.
0041#STR0041#ALL#To Cost Center?
0042#STR0042#ALL#can be filled out with Z up to  
0043#STR0043#ALL#the end to consider codes until the last one.
0044#STR0044#ALL#From Environment?
0045#STR0045#ALL#Environment code. The field 
0046#STR0046#ALL#To Environment?
0047#STR0047#ALL#From Evaluation Date?
0048#STR0048#ALL#Minimum date of risk evaluation.
0049#STR0049#ALL#To Evaluation Date?
0050#STR0050#ALL#Maximum date of risk evaluation.
0051#STR0051#ALL#Risk Map:
0052#STR0052#ALL#CIPA
0053#STR0053#ALL#SESMT
0054#STR0054#ALL#Both
0055#STR0055#ALL#Defines if risks to be considered are only the ones in map developed by CIPA or CIPATR, 
0056#STR0056#ALL#or only those in map developed by SESMT, or risks of both cases.
0057#STR0057#ALL#Consider:
0058#STR0058#ALL#OHC
0059#STR0059#ALL#None
0060#STR0060#ALL#ASO and PPP
0061#STR0061#ALL#PPP
0062#STR0062#ALL#Defines the type of risks considered for each option, being: 
0063#STR0063#ALL#ASO: will filter the ones that are only 'ASO' and 'ASO and PPP'; None: will filter the ones that are only 'None' and the risks that have field Consider equal to Blank. 
0064#STR0064#ALL#ASO and PPP: will filter the ones that are only 'PPP', 'ASO' and 'ASO and PPP'; PPP: will filter the ones that only 'PPP' and 'ASO and PPP'.
